\subtree[fre-2110]{
\taxon{Definition}
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\title{Preidempotent maps}

\p{
A \em{preidempotent map} is a map #{f : X \to X} such that #{f \circ f \sim f}. The
data of a [homotopy](stt-001M) #{f \circ f \sim f} is called a \em{preidempotence}.
}
\p{
In set-level mathematics, this concept is better known as an "idempotent map".
However, in homotopical mathematics such as our present setting, the preidempotence
condition #{f \circ f \sim f} is not enough to ensure a well-behaved notion of
idempotence in general. For instance, one would expect idempotents to split, but this
is not true for all preidempotent maps in the homotopical setting of univalent
foundations. Instead, we must ask for additional data to ensure the homotopy
#{f \circ f \sim f} itself is well-enough behaved. This leads to the definitions of
[quasiidempotent](fre-9876) and [(coherently) idempotent](fre-9874) maps.
}
\p{
Our terminology follows that of [[michaelshulman]] \citek{shulman-idempotents-2017}
and so we designate the somewhat derogatory term "preidempotent" for the reason
described above.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
preidempotence
  : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď§} ‚Üí (X ‚Üí X) ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
preidempotence f = f ‚ąė f ~ f

preidempotent-map
  : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} ‚Üí Type ūĚď§ ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
preidempotent-map X = ő£[ f ‚ą∂ (X ‚Üí X) ] preidempotence f
}
% ```
}

\subtree[fre-9876]{
\taxon{Definition}
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\title{Quasiidempotent maps}

\p{
A map #{f : X \to X} is \em{quasiidempotent} if it comes equipped with a
\em{quasiidempotence}: a [homotopy](stt-001M) #{I : f \circ f \sim f} such that
#{f I \sim I f}.
}
\p{
While the single extra condition of #{f I \sim I f} compared to
[preidempotent maps](fre-2110) is not enough for the notion of quasiidempotence to
present a fully coherent notion of idempotence of maps in homotopical mathematics, it
\em{is} enough for us to be able to show [that #{f} splits](fre-2113). We show this
following [[michaelshulman]]'s work \citek{shulman-idempotents-2017}.
}
\p{
Our terminology follows that of [[michaelshulman]] \citek{shulman-idempotents-2017}
and so we designate the somewhat derogatory term "quasiidempotent" for the reason
described above.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
qcoh-preidempotence
  : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď§} (f : X ‚Üí X)
  ‚Üí preidempotence f
  ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
qcoh-preidempotence f I = (f ‚óā I) ~ (I ‚Ėł f)

qidempotence
  : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď§}
  ‚Üí (X ‚Üí X) ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
qidempotence f = ő£[ I ‚ą∂ preidempotence f ] qcoh-preidempotence f I

qidempotent-map
  : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} ‚Üí Type ūĚď§ ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
qidempotent-map X = ő£[ f ‚ą∂ (X ‚Üí X) ] qidempotence f
}
% ```
}

\subtree{
\taxon{Theorem}
\date{2026-03-17}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\title{Equality of quasiidempotences}

\p{
Equalities of quasiidempotences are characterised by homotopies between the
underlying preidempotences together with a compatible homotopy between the
quasicoherences.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
module _ {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X} where

  qidempotence-coherence
    : (H K : qidempotence f)
    ‚Üí (H .fst ~ K .fst)
    ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
  qidempotence-coherence H K ŌĀ
    = (H .snd ~‚ąô ŌĀ ‚ąė f) ~ (ap (ap f) ‚ąė ŌĀ ~‚ąô K .snd)

  qidempotence-htpy
    : qidempotence f
    ‚Üí qidempotence f
    ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
  qidempotence-htpy H K
    = ő£[ ŌĀ ‚ą∂ H .fst ~ K .fst ] qidempotence-coherence H K ŌĀ

  refl-qidempotence-htpy
    : (H : qidempotence f)
    ‚Üí qidempotence-htpy H H
  refl-qidempotence-htpy (I , Q)
    = ~refl
    , (őĽ x ‚Üí ‚ąô-reflr (Q x) ‚ąô sym (‚ąô-refll (Q x)))

module QIdempotenceWithFunExt (FE : FunExt-global) where
  open WithFunExt-global FE
  module EP = EProp FE
  open EP

  module _
    {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X}
    (H : qidempotence f)
    where

    qidempotence-htpy-is-torsorial
      : is-singleton (ő£[ K ‚ą∂ qidempotence f ] qidempotence-htpy H K)
    qidempotence-htpy-is-torsorial
      = is-singleton-structure‚Üźparts
          (htpy-is-torsorial FE (H .fst))
          (_ , ~refl)
          (is-single‚Üźequiv-to-single
            (ő£-ap-‚ČÉ-fst (HEquiv.~‚ąô‚ČÉ FE ~refl))
            (htpy-is-torsorial FE (H .snd ~‚ąô ~refl)))

  qidempotence-htpy‚ÜźId
    : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X}
      {H K : qidempotence f}
    ‚Üí H ÔľĚ K
    ‚Üí qidempotence-htpy H K
  qidempotence-htpy‚ÜźId {H = H} refl
    = refl-qidempotence-htpy H

  qidempotence-htpy-is-equiv
    : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X}
      (H K : qidempotence f)
    ‚Üí is-equiv (qidempotence-htpy‚ÜźId {H = H} {K = K})
  qidempotence-htpy-is-equiv H
    = fundamental-Id
        (qidempotence-htpy H)
        (qidempotence-htpy-is-torsorial H)
        (őĽ _ ‚Üí qidempotence-htpy‚ÜźId)

  Id‚ČÉqidempotence-htpy
    : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X}
      (H K : qidempotence f)
    ‚Üí (H ÔľĚ K) ‚ČÉ qidempotence-htpy H K
  Id‚ČÉqidempotence-htpy H K
    = mk‚ČÉ qidempotence-htpy‚ÜźId (qidempotence-htpy-is-equiv H K)

  Id‚Üźqidempotence-htpy
    : ‚ąÄ {ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X}
      {H K : qidempotence f}
    ‚Üí qidempotence-htpy H K
    ‚Üí H ÔľĚ K
  Id‚Üźqidempotence-htpy {H = H} {K = K}
    = _‚ČÉ_.bwd (Id‚ČÉqidempotence-htpy H K)
}
% ```
}

\subtree[fre-9875]{
\taxon{Theorem}
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\title{Limit presentation of quasiidempotent maps}

\p{
We present the type of [quasiidempotent maps](fre-9876) as a [pullback](stt-003I).
A preidempotent map #{(f,I)} determines, for each #{x : X}, a pair of identifications
in the total identity type of #{X}, #{\Sigma_{(x,y : X)}(x = y)}:
namely the equality #{\ap_f(I(x)) : f(f(f(x))) = f(f(x))} and the equality
#{I(f(x)) : f(f(f(x))) = f(f(x))}. Equivalently, these are two points of the total
identity type lying over the same pair #{(f(f(f(x))),f(f(x)))}. A quasicoherence of
the preidempotence is exactly a family of fillers between these two identifications.
}

\p{
Therefore, #{\textsf{QIdem}(X)} is the pullback of the boundary map of a
preidempotent map against the forgetful map from fillers to their boundaries:
\quiver{
\begin{tikzcd}
		\textsf{QIdem}(X) && (X \to \textsf{QData}(X)) \\
		\\
	\textsf{PreIdem}(X) && (X \to \textsf{QBoundary}(X))
	\arrow[from=1-1, to=1-3]
	\arrow[from=1-1, to=3-1]
	\arrow["{\fst^X}", from=1-3, to=3-3]
	\arrow["\textsf{boundary}", from=3-1, to=3-3]
	\arrow["\lrcorner" very near start, phantom, from=1-1, to=3-3]
\end{tikzcd}
}
Here #{\textsf{boundary}} is the map formalised as \code{quasicoherence-boundary-map}.
}

\agda{
quasicoherence-boundary
  : {ūĚď§ : Level}
  ‚Üí Type ūĚď§ ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
quasicoherence-boundary X
  = ő£[ uv ‚ą∂ (total-Id X √ó total-Id X) ]
      (uv .fst .fst ÔľĚ uv .snd .fst)

quasicoherence-filler
  : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
  ‚Üí quasicoherence-boundary X
  ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
quasicoherence-filler ((u , v) , p)
  = IdŠĶą
      ( ap (őĽ (x , y) ‚Üí x ÔľĚ y) p)
      ( u .snd)
      ( v .snd)

quasicoherence-data
  : {ūĚď§ : Level} ‚Üí Type ūĚď§ ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
quasicoherence-data X
  = ő£[ B ‚ą∂ quasicoherence-boundary X ] quasicoherence-filler B

quasicoherence-boundary-map
  : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
  ‚Üí preidempotent-map X
  ‚Üí (a : X)
  ‚Üí quasicoherence-boundary X
quasicoherence-boundary-map (f , I) a
  = ( ( ((f (f (f a)) , f (f a)) , ap f (I a))
      , ((f (f (f a)) , f (f a)) , I (f a)))
    , refl)

quasicoherence-data‚ČÉtotal-Id
  : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
  ‚Üí quasicoherence-data X
  ‚ČÉ total-Id (total-Id X)
quasicoherence-data‚ČÉtotal-Id
  = ő£-assoc ‚ąô‚ČÉ ő£-ap-‚ČÉ (őĽ _ ‚Üí ő£-path)

quasicoherence-data‚ČÉ
  : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
  ‚Üí quasicoherence-data X ‚ČÉ X
quasicoherence-data‚ČÉ {X = X}
  = quasicoherence-data‚ČÉtotal-Id
  ‚ąô‚ČÉ total-Id‚ČÉ {X = total-Id X}
  ‚ąô‚ČÉ total-Id‚ČÉ {X = X}

module QIdemWithFunExt (FE : FunExt-global) where
  open WithFunExt-global FE

  quasicoherence-filler‚ČÉfibre
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
      (B : quasicoherence-boundary X)
    ‚Üí quasicoherence-filler B
    ‚ČÉ fibre fst B
  quasicoherence-filler‚ČÉfibre {X = X} B
    = fibre-straighten {A = quasicoherence-boundary X} quasicoherence-filler B e‚ĀĽ¬Ļ

  quasicoherence-forget
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
    ‚Üí (X ‚Üí quasicoherence-data X)
    ‚Üí (X ‚Üí quasicoherence-boundary X)
  quasicoherence-forget = fst ‚ąė_

  quasicoherence-forget-fibre‚Üźqcoh-preidempotence
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X}
      (I : preidempotence f)
    ‚Üí qcoh-preidempotence f I
    ‚Üí fibre
        (quasicoherence-forget {X = X})
        (quasicoherence-boundary-map (f , I))
  quasicoherence-forget-fibre‚Üźqcoh-preidempotence {X = X} {f = f} I
    = _‚ČÉ_.fwd
        ( EProp.ő†-ap-‚ČÉ FE {A = X} (őĽ a
          ‚Üí quasicoherence-filler‚ČÉfibre (quasicoherence-boundary-map (f , I) a))
        ‚ąô‚ČÉ ő£-ő†-swap‚ČÉ _ _
        ‚ąô‚ČÉ ő£-ap-‚ČÉ (őĽ _ ‚Üí funext‚ČÉ e‚ĀĽ¬Ļ))

  qcoh-preidempotence‚ČÉquasicoherence-forget-fibre
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X}
      (I : preidempotence f)
    ‚Üí qcoh-preidempotence f I
    ‚ČÉ fibre
        (quasicoherence-forget {X = X})
        (quasicoherence-boundary-map (f , I))
  qcoh-preidempotence‚ČÉquasicoherence-forget-fibre {X = X} {f = f} I
    = mk‚ČÉ
        (quasicoherence-forget-fibre‚Üźqcoh-preidempotence {X = X} {f = f} I)
        (_‚ČÉ_.has-is-eqv
          ( EProp.ő†-ap-‚ČÉ FE {A = X}
              (quasicoherence-filler‚ČÉfibre ‚ąė quasicoherence-boundary-map (f , I))
          ‚ąô‚ČÉ ő£-ő†-swap‚ČÉ _ _
          ‚ąô‚ČÉ ő£-ap-‚ČÉ (őĽ _ ‚Üí funext‚ČÉ e‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)))

  qidempotent-map-pullback-cone
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
    ‚Üí Cone
        (mk-cospan
          (X ‚Üí quasicoherence-boundary X)
          (quasicoherence-forget {X = X})
          (quasicoherence-boundary-map {X = X}))
        (qidempotent-map X)
  qidempotent-map-pullback-cone {X = X}
    = mk-cone
        (őĽ (f , I , Q)
         ‚Üí quasicoherence-forget-fibre‚Üźqcoh-preidempotence {f = f} I Q .fst)
        (őĽ (f , I , _) ‚Üí (f , I))
        (őĽ (f , I , Q)
         ‚Üí quasicoherence-forget-fibre‚Üźqcoh-preidempotence {f = f} I Q .snd)

  qidempotent-map-pullback-gap
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
    ‚Üí qidempotent-map X
    ‚Üí Pullback
        (quasicoherence-forget {X = X})
        (quasicoherence-boundary-map {X = X})
  qidempotent-map-pullback-gap {X = X}
    = gap (qidempotent-map-pullback-cone {X = X})

  qidempotent-map-pullback-gap-is-equiv
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
    ‚Üí is-equiv (qidempotent-map-pullback-gap {X = X})
  qidempotent-map-pullback-gap-is-equiv {X = X} = is-equiv‚Üźqiso qiso where

    qiso
      : quasi-iso (qidempotent-map-pullback-gap {X = X})
    qiso .fst (Q , (f , I) , p)
      = f , I
      , _‚ČÉ_.bwd
          (qcoh-preidempotence‚ČÉquasicoherence-forget-fibre {X = X} {f = f} I)
          (Q , p)
    qiso .snd .fst (f , I , Q)
      = ap
          (őĽ r ‚Üí f , I , r)
          (is-equiv.ő∑ (_‚ČÉ_.has-is-eqv (qcoh-preidempotence‚ČÉquasicoherence-forget-fibre {X = X} {f = f} I)) Q)
    qiso .snd .snd (Q , (f , I) , p)
      = ap
          (őĽ r ‚Üí fst r , (f , I) , snd r)
          (is-equiv.őĶ
            (_‚ČÉ_.has-is-eqv (qcoh-preidempotence‚ČÉquasicoherence-forget-fibre {X = X} {f = f} I))
            (Q , p))

  qidempotent-map‚ČÉpullback
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
    ‚Üí qidempotent-map X
    ‚ČÉ Pullback
        (quasicoherence-forget {X = X})
        (quasicoherence-boundary-map {X = X})
  qidempotent-map‚ČÉpullback {X = X}
    = mk‚ČÉ
        (qidempotent-map-pullback-gap)
        (qidempotent-map-pullback-gap-is-equiv {X = X})
}
% ```
}

\subtree{
\taxon{Construction}
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\title{The sequential splitting of a preidempotent map}

\p{
Given a map #{f : A \to A}, then we may form its
\em{sequential splitting} as the [sequential limit](Foundations.CanonicalSeqLim) of
the [tower](Foundations.Tower)
##{\cdots \to A \xrightarrow{f} A \to \cdots \to A \xrightarrow{f} A,}
i.e., the type of sequences #{a} of elements of #{A} such that #{a_i = f(a_{i+1})}
for all #{i}. When #{f} is [preidempotent](fre-2110) this type factors #{f}.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
module Splitting
  {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}
  (f : X ‚Üí X)
  where

  type : Type ūĚď§
  type = Seq-lim (tower‚Üźendomap f)

  inclusion : type ‚Üí X
  inclusion = limit-point (tower‚Üźendomap f)

  shift : type ‚Üí type
  shift (a , őĪ)
    = ( (őĽ n ‚Üí f (f (a (suc n))))
      , (őĽ n ‚Üí ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n))))

  map-retraction
    : preidempotence f
    ‚Üí X ‚Üí type
  map-retraction I x
    = ((őĽ _ ‚Üí f x) , (őĽ _ ‚Üí sym (I x)))

  factorisation
    : (I : preidempotence f)
    ‚Üí inclusion ‚ąė map-retraction I ~ f
  factorisation I x = refl
}
% ```
}

\subtree[fre-2112]{
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\taxon{Theorem}
\title{Retracts give quasiidempotent maps}

\p{
A retract #{A \xrightarrow{i} X \xrightarrow{r} A} such that #{r \circ i \sim \id}
determines a quasiidempotent map on #{X}, #{i \circ r}.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
module _ {ūĚď§ ūĚď• : Level} {A : Type ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď•} where

  retraction-htpy-nat
    : {i : A ‚Üí X} {r : X ‚Üí A} (rs : r ‚ąė i ~ id)
    ‚Üí (x : X) ‚Üí ap r (ap i (rs (r x))) ÔľĚ rs (r (i (r x)))
  retraction-htpy-nat {i = i} {r = r} rs x
    = ap r (ap i p)
        ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-reflr (ap r (ap i p))) ‚ü©
      ap r (ap i p) ‚ąô refl
        ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (ap r (ap i p) ‚ąô_) (sym (‚ąô-sym p)) ‚ü©
      ap r (ap i p) ‚ąô (p ‚ąô sym p)
        ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-assoc (ap r (ap i p)) p (sym p)) ‚ü©
      (ap r (ap i p) ‚ąô p) ‚ąô sym p
        ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô sym p) (sym nat-rs) ‚ü©
      (rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąô p) ‚ąô sym p
        ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô-assoc (rs (r (i (r x)))) p (sym p) ‚ü©
      rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąô (p ‚ąô sym p)
        ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąô_) (‚ąô-sym p) ‚ü©
      rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąô refl
        ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô-reflr (rs (r (i (r x)))) ‚ü©
      rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąé where

    p : r (i (r x)) ÔľĚ r x
    p = rs (r x)

    nat-rs
      : rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąô p
      ÔľĚ ap r (ap i p) ‚ąô p
    nat-rs
      = rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąô p
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąô_) (sym (ap-id p)) ‚ü©
        rs (r (i (r x))) ‚ąô ap id p
          ÔľĚ‚ü® homotopy-natural rs p ‚ü©
        ap (r ‚ąė i) p ‚ąô rs (r x)
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô p) (ap-‚ąė r i p) ‚ü©
        ap r (ap i p) ‚ąô p ‚ąé

  quasiidempotence‚Üźsection-retraction
    : (i : A ‚Üí X) (r : X ‚Üí A)
      (rs : r ‚ąė i ~ id)
    ‚Üí qidempotence (i ‚ąė r)
  quasiidempotence‚Üźsection-retraction i r rs
    = I , Q where

    I : preidempotence (i ‚ąė r)
    I x = ap i (rs (r x))

    Q : qcoh-preidempotence (i ‚ąė r) I
    Q x = ap-‚ąė i r (I x) ‚ąô ap (ap i) (retraction-htpy-nat rs x)

  qidempotent-map‚Üźretract
    : retract A X
    ‚Üí qidempotent-map X
  qidempotent-map‚Üźretract (i , r , rs)
    = (i ‚ąė r , quasiidempotence‚Üźsection-retraction i r rs)
}
% ```
}

\subtree[fre-2113]{
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\taxon{Theorem}
\title{Splitting construction on quasiidempotent maps}

\p{
Any quasiidempotent map #{f : A \to A} splits its domain. I.e., there is a type
#{X} such that #{X} is a retract of #{A} and factors #{f}.
}

\p{
We show that the sequential limit of the [tower](Foundations.Tower)
##{\cdots \to A \xrightarrow{f} A \to \cdots \to A \xrightarrow{f} A}
is a retract of #{A} that factors #{f}, following
\citet{Thm 5.3}{shulman-idempotents-2017}.
}

\p{
The construction uses two different levels of coherence. The type
#{\textsf{Splitting.type}(f)} and its inclusion into #{A} were already defined
above for any endomap #{f}. Moreover, a preidempotence #{I : f \circ f \sim f} alone
already gives the converse map
#{\textsf{Splitting.map-retraction}(I) : A \to \textsf{Splitting.type}(f)}
and the factorisation #{i \circ r \sim f}. What remains is to show that,
assuming a full quasiidempotence, this converse map is also a retraction of the
inclusion.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
module IdemWithFunExt (FE : FunExt-global) where
  open WithFunExt-global FE
  open LimitWithFunExt FE

  module _ {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§} {f : X ‚Üí X} (H : qidempotence f) where
    open Splitting f

    path-shift-Splitting-type~id
      : (aőĪ : type)
      ‚Üí (n : ‚Ąē) ‚Üí f (f (aőĪ .fst (suc n))) ÔľĚ (aőĪ .fst n)
    path-shift-Splitting-type~id (a , őĪ) n
      = I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô sym (őĪ n)
      where
      I = H .fst
      Q = H .snd

    square-shift-Splitting-type~id
      : (aőĪ : type)
        (n : ‚Ąē)
      ‚Üí Square
          (path-shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ n)
          (ap f (path-shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ (suc n)))
          (ap (f ‚ąė f) (aőĪ .snd (suc n)))
          (aőĪ .snd n)
    square-shift-Splitting-type~id (a , őĪ) n = mk-square
      ( path-shift-Splitting-type~id (a , őĪ) n ‚ąô őĪ n
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô-assoc (I (a (suc n))) (sym (őĪ n)) (őĪ n) ‚ü©
        I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô (sym (őĪ n) ‚ąô őĪ n)
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô_) (‚ąô-sym' (őĪ n)) ‚ü©
        I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô refl
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô-reflr (I (a (suc n))) ‚ü©
        I (a (suc n))
          ÔľĚ‚ü® sym rhs‚ÜíI ‚ü©
        ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n))
        ‚ąô ap f (path-shift-Splitting-type~id (a , őĪ) (suc n)) ‚ąé)
      where
      I = H .fst
      Q = H .snd

      rhs‚ÜíI
        : ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n))
        ‚ąô ap f (path-shift-Splitting-type~id (a , őĪ) (suc n))
        ÔľĚ I (a (suc n))
      rhs‚ÜíI
        = ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n))
          ‚ąô ap f (path-shift-Splitting-type~id (a , őĪ) (suc n))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô_)
                  (ap-‚ąô f (I (a (suc (suc n)))) (sym (őĪ (suc n)))) ‚ü©
          ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n))
          ‚ąô (ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))) ‚ąô ap f (sym (őĪ (suc n))))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô_)
                  (ap (ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))) ‚ąô_)
                      (ap-sym f (őĪ (suc n)))) ‚ü©
          ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n))
          ‚ąô (ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))) ‚ąô sym (ap f (őĪ (suc n))))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-assoc _ _ _) ‚ü©
          ( ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))))
          ‚ąô sym (ap f (őĪ (suc n)))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô sym (ap f (őĪ (suc n))))
                  (ap (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô_)
                      (Q (a (suc (suc n))))) ‚ü©
          ( ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô I (f (a (suc (suc n)))))
          ‚ąô sym (ap f (őĪ (suc n)))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô sym (ap f (őĪ (suc n))))
                  (sym (homotopy-natural I (őĪ (suc n)))) ‚ü©
          (I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (őĪ (suc n))) ‚ąô sym (ap f (őĪ (suc n)))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô.cancell _ (‚ąô-sym (ap f (őĪ (suc n)))) ‚ü©
          I (a (suc n)) ‚ąé

    opaque
      shift-Splitting-type~id
        : shift ~ id
      shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ
        = Id‚ÜźSeq-lim-htpy
            ( tower‚Üźendomap f)
            ( path-shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ
            , square-shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ)

      ap-inclusion-shift-Splitting-type~id
        : (aőĪ : type)
        ‚Üí ap inclusion
             (shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ)
        ÔľĚ path-shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ 0
      ap-inclusion-shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ
        = ap-limit-point-Id‚ÜźSeq-lim-htpy
            ( tower‚Üźendomap f)
            ( path-shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ
            , square-shift-Splitting-type~id aőĪ)
}
% ```

\p{
We first introduce the shift endomap on the splitting type. On a coherent sequence
#{(a,\alpha)}, it discards the initial entry and then whiskers the tail by
#{f \circ f}. The quasicoherence data are used exactly to show that this shift is
homotopic to the identity, first levelwise by
\code{path-shift-Splitting-type~id}, and then coherently by
\code{square-shift-Splitting-type~id}. Function extensionality and the universal
property of sequential limits turn these data into
\code{shift-Splitting-type~id}.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
    path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type
      : (aőĪ : type)
      ‚Üí (n : ‚Ąē) ‚Üí f (aőĪ .fst 0) ÔľĚ f (f (aőĪ .fst (suc n)))
    path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type (a , őĪ) 0
      = ap f (őĪ 0)
    path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type (a , őĪ) (suc n)
      = path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type (a , őĪ) n
      ‚ąô I (a (suc n))
      ‚ąô ap f (őĪ (suc n))
      where
      I = H .fst
      Q = H .snd

    square-compute-retraction-Splitting-type
      : (aőĪ : type)
        (n : ‚Ąē)
      ‚Üí Square
          (path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ n)
          (ap f (path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ (suc n)))
          (sym (H .fst (aőĪ .fst 0)))
          (ap (f ‚ąė f) (aőĪ .snd (suc n)))
    square-compute-retraction-Splitting-type (a , őĪ) 0
      = mk-square (sym rhs) where
      I = H .fst
      Q = H .snd

      őĺ : (n : ‚Ąē) ‚Üí f (a 0) ÔľĚ f (f (a (suc n)))
      őĺ = path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type (a , őĪ)

      step
        : ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 0) ‚ąô ap f (I (a 1))
        ÔľĚ I (a 0) ‚ąô ap f (őĪ 0)
      step
        = ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 0) ‚ąô ap f (I (a 1))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 0) ‚ąô_) (Q (a 1)) ‚ü©
        ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 0) ‚ąô I (f (a 1))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (homotopy-natural I (őĪ 0)) ‚ü©
        I (a 0) ‚ąô ap f (őĪ 0) ‚ąé

      rhs
        : sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô ap f (őĺ 1)
        ÔľĚ őĺ 0 ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1)
      rhs
        = sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô ap f (őĺ 1)
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô_)
                   (ap-‚ąô‚ąô f (őĺ 0) (I (a 1)) (ap f (őĪ 1))) ‚ü©
        sym (I (a 0))
        ‚ąô (ap f (őĺ 0) ‚ąô ap f (I (a 1)) ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ 1)))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô_)
                (ap (őĽ q ‚Üí ap f (őĺ 0) ‚ąô (ap f (I (a 1)) ‚ąô q))
                    (sym (ap-‚ąė f f (őĪ 1)))) ‚ü©
        sym (I (a 0))
        ‚ąô (ap f (őĺ 0) ‚ąô ap f (I (a 1)) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô_)
                (sym (‚ąô-assoc (ap f (őĺ 0)) (ap f (I (a 1)))
                      (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1)))
                 ‚ąô ap (_‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))
                      (ap (_‚ąô ap f (I (a 1))) (sym (ap-‚ąė f f (őĪ 0))))) ‚ü©
        sym (I (a 0))
        ‚ąô ( (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 0) ‚ąô ap f (I (a 1)))
          ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô_) (ap (_‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1)) step) ‚ü©
        sym (I (a 0))
          ‚ąô ((I (a 0) ‚ąô ap f (őĪ 0))
            ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô_)
                   (‚ąô-assoc (I (a 0)) (ap f (őĪ 0)) (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))) ‚ü©
        sym (I (a 0))
        ‚ąô (I (a 0) ‚ąô (ap f (őĪ 0) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1)))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-assoc (sym (I (a 0))) (I (a 0))
                     (ap f (őĪ 0) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))) ‚ü©
        (sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô I (a 0))
        ‚ąô (ap f (őĪ 0) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô (ap f (őĪ 0) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))) (‚ąô-sym' (I (a 0))) ‚ü©
        refl ‚ąô (ap f (őĪ 0) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô-refll _ ‚ü©
        őĺ 0 ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ 1) ‚ąé
}
% ```


\p{
For the inductive step we fill the following diagram, following
\citek{shulman-idempotents-2017}:

\quiver{
\begin{tikzcd}
	f(a_0) &&& f(f(a_{n+1})) &&& f(a_{n+1}) \\
	\\
	f(f(a_0)) &&& f(f(f(a_{n+2}))) &&& f(f(a_{n+2}))
	\arrow["{\xi_{n+1}}", from=1-1, to=1-4]
	\arrow["{I(a_{n+1})}", from=1-4, to=1-7]
	\arrow["{I(a_0)^{-1}}"', from=1-1, to=3-1]
	\arrow["{f(f(\alpha_{n+1}))}" description, from=1-4, to=3-4]
	\arrow["{f(\alpha_{n+1})}", from=1-7, to=3-7]
	\arrow["{f(\xi_n) \cdot I(a_{n+1}) \cdot f(\alpha_{n+1})}"', from=3-1, to=3-4]
	\arrow["{I(f(a_{n+2}))}", from=3-4, to=3-7, shift left=2]
	\arrow["{f(I(a_{n+2}))}"', from=3-4, to=3-7, shift right=2]
	\arrow["Q"{anchor=center, pos=.45}, draw=none, from=3-4, to=3-7]
	\arrow["{\Xi_n}"{anchor=center, pos=.45}, draw=none, from=1-1, to=3-4]
	\arrow["{\text{naturality}}"{anchor=center, pos=.45}, draw=none, from=1-4, to=3-7]
\end{tikzcd}
}
}

\ul{
\li{#{\xi} is formalised as \code{path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type}.}
\li{#{\Xi} is formalised as \code{square-compute-retraction-Splitting-type}.}
}

\p{
In particular, the left-hand square labelled #{\Xi_n} is the inductive hypothesis.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
    square-compute-retraction-Splitting-type (a , őĪ) (suc n)
      = mk-square (sym rhs) where
      I = H .fst
      Q = H .snd
      őĺ = path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type (a , őĪ)
      őě = square-compute-retraction-Splitting-type (a , őĪ)

      step
        : ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (I (a (suc (suc n))))
        ÔľĚ I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (őĪ (suc n))
      step
        = ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (I (a (suc (suc n))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô_) (Q (a (suc (suc n)))) ‚ü©
        ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô I (f (a (suc (suc n))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (homotopy-natural I (őĪ (suc n))) ‚ü©
        I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąé

      rhs
        : sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô ap f (őĺ (suc (suc n)))
        ÔľĚ őĺ (suc n) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc (suc n)))
      rhs
        = sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô ap f (őĺ (suc (suc n)))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô_)
                   (ap-‚ąô‚ąô f (őĺ (suc n)) (I (a (suc (suc n)))) (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n))))) ‚ü©
        sym (I (a 0))
        ‚ąô (ap f (őĺ (suc n))
          ‚ąô ap f (I (a (suc (suc n))))
          ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n)))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-assoc _ _ _) ‚ü©
        ( sym (I (a 0)) ‚ąô ap f (őĺ (suc n)))
        ‚ąô (ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))) ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n)))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô (ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))) ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n))))))
                   (sym (un-square (őě n))) ‚ü©
        ( őĺ n ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)))
        ‚ąô (ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))) ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n)))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô-assoc _ _ _ ‚ü©
        őĺ n
        ‚ąô (ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n))
        ‚ąô (ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))) ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n))))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (őĺ n ‚ąô_) (sym (‚ąô-assoc _ _ _)) ‚ü©
        őĺ n
        ‚ąô ((ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (I (a (suc (suc n)))))
        ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n)))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (őĽ q ‚Üí őĺ n ‚ąô (q ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n)))))) step ‚ü©
        őĺ n
        ‚ąô ((I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (őĪ (suc n)))
        ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n)))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (őĺ n ‚ąô_) (‚ąô-assoc _ _ _) ‚ü©
        őĺ n
        ‚ąô (I (a (suc n))
        ‚ąô (ap f (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô ap f (ap f (őĪ (suc (suc n))))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (őĽ q ‚Üí őĺ n ‚ąô (I (a (suc n)) ‚ąô (ap f (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô q)))
                (sym (ap-‚ąė f f (őĪ (suc (suc n))))) ‚ü©
        őĺ n
        ‚ąô ( I (a (suc n))
          ‚ąô (ap f (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc (suc n)))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-assoc _ _ _) ‚ü©
        ( őĺ n ‚ąô I (a (suc n)))
        ‚ąô (ap f (őĪ (suc n)) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc (suc n))))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-assoc _ _ _) ‚ü©
        ( ( őĺ n ‚ąô I (a (suc n)))
          ‚ąô ap f (őĪ (suc n)))
        ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc (suc n)))
            ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc (suc n)))) (‚ąô-assoc _ _ _) ‚ü©
        őĺ (suc n) ‚ąô ap (f ‚ąė f) (őĪ (suc (suc n))) ‚ąé
}
% ```

\p{
Taken together, the base case and the inductive step produce a coherent homotopy from
the composite
#{\textsf{Splitting.map-retraction}(\fst H) \circ \textsf{Splitting.inclusion}}
to the shift.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
    opaque
      compute-retraction-Splitting-type
        : map-retraction (H .fst)
        ‚ąė inclusion
        ~ shift
      compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ
        = Id‚ÜźSeq-lim-htpy
            ( tower‚Üźendomap f)
            ( path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ
            , square-compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ)

      ap-inclusion-compute-retraction-Splitting-type
        : (aőĪ : type)
        ‚Üí ap inclusion
            (compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ)
        ÔľĚ path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ 0
      ap-inclusion-compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ
        = ap-limit-point-Id‚ÜźSeq-lim-htpy
            ( tower‚Üźendomap f)
            ( path-compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ
            , square-compute-retraction-Splitting-type aőĪ)
}
% ```

\p{
The retracting homotopy is now obtained by composing the comparison
\code{compute-retraction-Splitting-type} with the previously constructed
\code{shift-Splitting-type~id}. This yields the promised retract of #{A} by its
sequential splitting type.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
    retract-Splitting-type
      : retract (type) X
    retract-Splitting-type
      = ( inclusion
        , map-retraction (H .fst)
        , compute-retraction-Splitting-type ~‚ąô shift-Splitting-type~id)
}
% ```
}

\subtree[fre-2114]{
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\taxon{Theorem}
\title{The splitting construction of a retract is a retract}

\p{
If a quasiidempotent comes from an actual retract, then its sequential splitting
carrier retracts back to the original carrier.
}

\p{
This theorem is due to [[michaelshulman]] \citet{Thm 6.2}{shulman-idempotents-2017}.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
module SplitRetractWithFunExt (FE : FunExt-global) where
  open IdemWithFunExt FE
  open LimitWithFunExt FE
  open RetractWithFunExt FE

  module _
    {ūĚď§ ūĚď•} {A : Type ūĚď§} {X : Type ūĚď•}
    (R@(s , r , rs) : retract A X)
    (let Hq = snd (qidempotent-map‚Üźretract R))
    (let L = retract-Splitting-type Hq)
    (let w = L .snd .snd)
    where
    open Splitting (s ‚ąė r)

    map-section-retract-Splitting-type
      : A ‚Üí type
    map-section-retract-Splitting-type a
      = ((őĽ _ ‚Üí s a) , (őĽ _ ‚Üí sym (ap s (rs a))))

    retract-Splitting-type‚Üźretract
      : retract (type) A
    retract-Splitting-type‚Üźretract
      = ( r ‚ąė inclusion
        , map-section-retract-Splitting-type
        , compute-retraction-Splitting-type (snd (qidempotent-map‚Üźretract R))
        ~‚ąô shift-Splitting-type~id (snd (qidempotent-map‚Üźretract R)))

    split-retract-equiv
      : type ‚ČÉ A
    split-retract-equiv
      = mk‚ČÉ
          (r ‚ąė inclusion)
          (is-equiv‚Üźqiso qiso) where
      qiso : quasi-iso (r ‚ąė inclusion)
      qiso .fst = map-section-retract-Splitting-type
      qiso .snd .fst = retract-Splitting-type‚Üźretract .snd .snd
      qiso .snd .snd x = rs x

    compare-splittings-inclusion
      : L .fst
      ~ comp-retract (retract‚Üźequiv split-retract-equiv) R .fst
    compare-splittings-inclusion z
      = sym (ap (L .fst) (w z))

    compare-splittings-retraction
      : L .snd .fst
      ~ comp-retract (retract‚Üźequiv split-retract-equiv) R .snd .fst
    compare-splittings-retraction = ~refl

    nat-rs‚Üźretract
      : ‚ąÄ {x y : X}
        (p : x ÔľĚ (s ‚ąė r) y)
      ‚Üí rs (r x) ‚ąô ap r p
        ÔľĚ ap ((r ‚ąė s) ‚ąė r) p
        ‚ąô rs (r ((s ‚ąė r) y))
    nat-rs‚Üźretract {x = x} {y} p
      = rs (r x) ‚ąô ap r p
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (rs (r x) ‚ąô_) (sym (ap-id (ap r p))) ‚ü©
        rs (r x) ‚ąô ap id (ap r p)
          ÔľĚ‚ü® homotopy-natural rs (ap r p) ‚ü©
        ap (r ‚ąė s) (ap r p) ‚ąô rs (r ((s ‚ąė r) y))
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô rs (r ((s ‚ąė r) y))) (sym (ap-‚ąė (r ‚ąė s) r p)) ‚ü©
        ap ((r ‚ąė s) ‚ąė r) p ‚ąô rs (r ((s ‚ąė r) y)) ‚ąé

    compare-splittings-compute
      : (a : (n : ‚Ąē) ‚Üí X)
        (őĪ : (n : ‚Ąē) ‚Üí a n ÔľĚ (s ‚ąė r) (a (suc n)))
      ‚Üí ap (r ‚ąė inclusion)
            (compute-retraction-Splitting-type Hq (a , őĪ))
      ÔľĚ ap ((r ‚ąė s) ‚ąė r) (őĪ 0)
    compare-splittings-compute a őĪ
      = ap-‚ąė r inclusion
          (compute-retraction-Splitting-type Hq (a , őĪ))
      ‚ąô ap (ap r) (ap-inclusion-compute-retraction-Splitting-type Hq (a , őĪ))
      ‚ąô sym (ap-‚ąė r (s ‚ąė r) (őĪ 0))

    compare-splittings-shift
      : (a : (n : ‚Ąē) ‚Üí X)
        (őĪ : (n : ‚Ąē) ‚Üí a n ÔľĚ (s ‚ąė r) (a (suc n)))
      ‚Üí ap (r ‚ąė inclusion )
            (shift-Splitting-type~id Hq (a , őĪ))
      ÔľĚ ap r (fst Hq (a 1)) ‚ąô sym (ap r (őĪ 0))
    compare-splittings-shift a őĪ
      = ap-‚ąė r inclusion (shift-Splitting-type~id Hq (a , őĪ))
      ‚ąô ap (ap r) (ap-inclusion-shift-Splitting-type~id Hq (a , őĪ))
      ‚ąô ap-‚ąô r (fst Hq (a 1)) (sym (őĪ 0))
      ‚ąô ap (ap r (fst Hq (a 1)) ‚ąô_) (ap-sym r (őĪ 0))

    opaque
      unfolding compute-retraction-Splitting-type
      unfolding shift-Splitting-type~id

      compare-splittings-section
        : (z : type)
        ‚Üí ap (r ‚ąė inclusion) (w z)
        ÔľĚ rs (r (inclusion z))
      compare-splittings-section (a , őĪ)
        = ap (r ‚ąė inclusion) (w (a , őĪ))
              ÔľĚ‚ü®‚ü©
          ap ( r ‚ąė inclusion)
              ( compute-retraction-Splitting-type Hq (a , őĪ)
              ‚ąô shift-Splitting-type~id Hq (a , őĪ))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ap-‚ąô
                  (r ‚ąė inclusion)
                  (compute-retraction-Splitting-type Hq (a , őĪ))
                  (shift-Splitting-type~id Hq (a , őĪ)) ‚ü©
          ap (r ‚ąė inclusion)
             (compute-retraction-Splitting-type Hq (a , őĪ))
          ‚ąô ap (r ‚ąė inclusion)
              (shift-Splitting-type~id Hq (a , őĪ))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ap‚āā _‚ąô_
                  (compare-splittings-compute a őĪ)
                  (compare-splittings-shift a őĪ) ‚ü©
          ap ((r ‚ąė s) ‚ąė r) (őĪ 0)
          ‚ąô (ap r (fst Hq (a 1)) ‚ąô sym (ap r (őĪ 0)))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (ap ((r ‚ąė s) ‚ąė r) (őĪ 0) ‚ąô_)
                  (ap (_‚ąô sym (ap r (őĪ 0)))
                      (retraction-htpy-nat rs (a 1))) ‚ü©
          ap ((r ‚ąė s) ‚ąė r) (őĪ 0)
          ‚ąô (rs (r ((s ‚ąė r) (a 1))) ‚ąô sym (ap r (őĪ 0)))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-assoc _ _ _) ‚ü©
          (ap ((r ‚ąė s) ‚ąė r) (őĪ 0)
            ‚ąô rs (r ((s ‚ąė r) (a 1))))
          ‚ąô sym (ap r (őĪ 0))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô sym (ap r (őĪ 0))) (sym (nat-rs‚Üźretract (őĪ 0))) ‚ü©
          (rs (r (a 0)) ‚ąô ap r (őĪ 0))
          ‚ąô sym (ap r (őĪ 0))
              ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô.cancell _ (‚ąô-sym (ap r (őĪ 0))) ‚ü©
          rs (r (a 0))
          ‚ąé

    compare-splittings-map-retraction
      : (z : type)
      ‚Üí ap (L .snd .fst) (compare-splittings-inclusion z)
      ÔľĚ sym (ap (map-section-retract-Splitting-type)
                 (rs (r (inclusion z))))
    compare-splittings-map-retraction z
      = ap (L .snd .fst) (compare-splittings-inclusion z)
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap-sym (L .snd .fst) (ap inclusion (w z)) ‚ü©
        sym (ap (L .snd .fst) (ap inclusion (w z)))
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap
              ( sym)
              ( ap-‚ąė (map-section-retract-Splitting-type)
                     (r)
                     (ap inclusion (w z))
              ‚ąô ap
                  ( ap map-section-retract-Splitting-type)
                  ( sym (ap-‚ąė r inclusion (w z))
                  ‚ąô compare-splittings-section z)) ‚ü©
        sym (ap (map-section-retract-Splitting-type)
                (rs (r (inclusion z)))) ‚ąé

    compare-splittings-coherence
      : coherence-retract-htpy
          L
          (comp-retract (retract‚Üźequiv split-retract-equiv) R)
          compare-splittings-inclusion
          compare-splittings-retraction
    compare-splittings-coherence z
      = w z
          ÔľĚ‚ü® sym (‚ąô-refll (w z)) ‚ü©
        refl ‚ąô w z
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô w z) (sym (‚ąô-sym' p)) ‚ü©
        (sym p ‚ąô p) ‚ąô w z
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ‚ąô-assoc (sym p) p (w z) ‚ü©
        sym p ‚ąô (p ‚ąô w z)
          ÔľĚ‚ü® ap (_‚ąô (p ‚ąô w z)) (sym (compare-splittings-map-retraction z)) ‚ü©
        ( ap (L .snd .fst) (compare-splittings-inclusion z)
        ‚ąô (comp-retract (retract‚Üźequiv split-retract-equiv) R) .snd .snd z)
        ‚ąé where
      p : map-section-retract-Splitting-type
            ( r (s (r (inclusion z))))
        ÔľĚ map-section-retract-Splitting-type
            ( r (inclusion z))
      p = ap (map-section-retract-Splitting-type)
             (rs (r (inclusion z)))

    compare-splittings-htpy
      : retract-htpy
          ( retract-Splitting-type (snd (qidempotent-map‚Üźretract R)))
          ( comp-retract (retract‚Üźequiv split-retract-equiv) R)
    compare-splittings-htpy
      = ( compare-splittings-inclusion
        , compare-splittings-retraction
        , compare-splittings-coherence)
}
% ```
}

\subtree[fre-2167]{
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\taxon{Corollary}
\title{The universe of retracts is a retract of quasiidempotents}

\p{
Combining the [splitting construction](fre-2114) with the
[equality principle](fre-1A1C) for the [universe of retracts](fre-1A1D), we obtain a
[retract](fre-2115) from the universe of retracts of #{A} into the type of
[quasiidempotent maps](fre-9876) of #{A}.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
module RetractsQIdempotentsWithFunExtUnivalence
  (FE : FunExt-global)
  (UA : Univalence)
  where

  open IdemWithFunExt FE
  open SplitRetractWithFunExt FE
  open RetractsWithFunExtUnivalence FE UA

  qidempotent‚ÜźRetracts
    : {ūĚď§ ūĚď•  : Level} {A : Type ūĚď§}
    ‚Üí Retracts ūĚď• A
    ‚Üí qidempotent-map A
  qidempotent‚ÜźRetracts (_ , R) = qidempotent-map‚Üźretract R

  Retracts‚Üźqidempotent-map
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {A : Type ūĚď§}
    ‚Üí qidempotent-map A
    ‚Üí Retracts ūĚď§ A
  Retracts‚Üźqidempotent-map H
    = ( Splitting.type (H .fst)
      , retract-Splitting-type (H .snd))

  retracts-qidempotent-map-retract
    : {ūĚď§ : Level} {A : Type ūĚď§}
    ‚Üí retract (Retracts ūĚď§ A) (qidempotent-map A)
  retracts-qidempotent-map-retract
    = ( qidempotent‚ÜźRetracts
      , Retracts‚Üźqidempotent-map
      , őĽ (_ , R)
      ‚Üí Id‚ÜźRetracts-equiv (split-retract-equiv R
                          , compare-splittings-htpy R))
}
% ```
}

\subtree[fre-9874]{
\date{2026-03-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\taxon{Definition}
\title{Coherently idempotent maps}

\p{
A \em{(coherently) idempotent map} is a map #{f : X \to X} equipped with a sequence
of [quasiidempotences](fre-9876) #{H} indexed by the
[natural numbers](Foundations.Nat) such that #{H_n} is the [splitting](fre-2113) of
#{H_{n+1}} for all #{n}.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
module CoherentIdemWithFunExt (FE : FunExt-global) where
  open IdemWithFunExt FE

  module _ {ūĚď§ : Level} {X : Type ūĚď§}  where

    step-qidempotence
      : {f : X ‚Üí X} ‚Üí qidempotence f ‚Üí qidempotence f
    step-qidempotence H
      = snd (qidempotent-map‚Üźretract (retract-Splitting-type H))

    idempotence-coherence
      : {f : X ‚Üí X}
      ‚Üí (‚Ąē ‚Üí qidempotence f)
      ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
    idempotence-coherence {f = f} H
      = (n : ‚Ąē)
      ‚Üí qidempotence-htpy (H n) (step-qidempotence {f = f} (H (suc n)))

    idempotence
      : (X ‚Üí X) ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
    idempotence f
      = ő£[ H ‚ą∂ (‚Ąē ‚Üí qidempotence f) ] idempotence-coherence {f = f} H

  idempotent-map : {ūĚď§ : Level} ‚Üí Type ūĚď§ ‚Üí Type ūĚď§
  idempotent-map X = ő£[ f ‚ą∂ (X ‚Üí X) ] idempotence f
}
% ```
}
